b'' b'' b'' b'' b' a problem occurs when i try to create a window with a visual that is different' b' from the visual of the parent (which uses the default visual which is tc24).' b'' b'' b"you've got to set border_pixel in your window attributes. the default" b'is copyfromparent which gives the badmatch. do this:' b'' b'...' b'unsigned long valuemask;' b'...' b'/*' b"* if border_width is non-zero you'd better alloc a colour from cmap" b'* rather than use any old pixel value. also, use valuemask, it makes' b'* the code more obvious.' b'*/' b'attr.colormap cmap;' b'attr.border_pixel b'valuemask cwcolormap cwborderpixel;' b'win xcreatewindow(' b'dpy,' b'defaultrootwindow(dpy),' b'10,10,' b'width,height,' b'0,\t\t border width. see comment below b'8, depth b'inputoutput, class b'vinfo.visual, visual b'valuemask,' b'&attr' b');' b'' b'a note on border_width: your code looked like this:' b'' b' win xcreatewindow(' b' dpy,' b' defaultrootwindow(dpy),' b' b' width,height,' b' copyfromparent, border width b' depth b' inputoutput, class b' vinfo.visual, visual b' cwcolormap,' b' &attr' b' b'' b"border_width set to copyfromparent works but doesn't make sense." b'border_width should be an unsigned int. you get away with it because' b"copyfromparent is #define'ed to be zero in x.h. if it happened to be" b"defined as you'd get a very interesting looking window!" b'' b'du pont pixel systems ltd.' b'' 